Purchase options and add-ons

  • ENJOY AN IMMERSIVE AUDIO EXPERIENCE - Echo Studio now features spatial audio processing technology for a wider and more immersive audio experience. For stereo formats, Spatial audio processing technology creates a wider and more enveloping sound stage. Its 5 speakers produce powerful bass with improved clarity, dynamic midrange and crisp highs. Dolby Atmos technology adds space, clarity and depth.
  • USE VOICE CONTROL FOR YOUR MUSIC - Stream songs from Amazon Music, Apple Music, Spotify, Deezer and more. With Amazon Music HD, enjoy access to 90 million songs in lossless audio formats like HD or Ultra HD and select songs in spatial audio formats like Dolby Atmos.
  • ADAPTS TO ANY ROOM - Automatically senses the acoustics of your space, fine-tuning playback for optimal sound.
  • BUILT-IN SMART HOME HUB - Ask Alexa to control Zigbee-compatible devices.
  • READY TO HELP - Ask Alexa to play music, read the news and answer questions.
  • KEEP YOUR FAMILY IN SYNC - Use your Alexa devices like an intercom and talk to any room in the house using Drop In and Announcements.
  • DESIGNED TO PROTECT YOUR PRIVACY - Built with multiple layers of privacy protection and control, including a Microphone Off button that electronically disconnects the microphones.

Our best-sounding Echo speaker yet

You've never heard an Echo like this before. Echo Studio is the only Echo speaker that creates an immersive, 3-dimensional soundscape, wrapping you in studio-quality audio from every direction. You can also ask Alexa to set alarms, control compatible smart home devices, check the weather, play a song and more. Learn more about Alexa features.

Make your music sound incredible

Human ears care where sound is coming from. Echo Studio turns that evolutionary truth into a revolutionary advantage. Five strategically positioned speakers generate room-filling sound, sending different parts of the song to your ears from different directions. This means you can hear studio-quality music as the artist intended.

“Alexa, play the Best of Spatial Audio playlist.”

Experience room-filling sound

Spatial audio processing technology is customised to fit the acoustic design of Echo Studio, featuring stereo up-mixing and spatial virtualisation to provide immersive studio-quality sound for your stereo audio and home cinema system.

With room-adaption technology, Echo Studio automatically analyses the acoustics of your space, fine-tuning playback for optimal sound, no matter where it’s placed.

Enjoy your favourite audio content

Stream all of your favourite music, podcasts and audiobooks with Amazon Music, Apple Music, Spotify, Deezer and more. An Amazon Music Unlimited subscription gives you access to millions of songs in Ultra HD and a fast-growing collection of spatial audio.

Help keep your smart home connected

Built-in smart home hub

Connect to and manage your smart home with the built-in hub. Just power on compatible smart devices and say, “Alexa, discover my devices.” Alexa will automatically detect and set them up so you can control lights, plugs, and more with your voice. Echo Studio also supports every Works with Alexa device across multiple protocols including Zigbee and Matter. Learn more about the different ways you can connect your smart home device.

“Alexa, discover my devices.”

Alexa is happy to help

Make your life easier at home. Use your voice to set timers, add items to lists, and create calendar events and reminders. You can also check the news, weather or traffic. Ask for sports scores, film times, restaurant hours or information. Learn more about Alexa Productivity.

“Alexa, what's on my calendar?”

Do more with device pairing

Echo Studio + another Echo
Fill your home with music using compatible Echo devices in different rooms. Learn more about Multi-Room Audio.

Echo Studio + Fire TV
Watch TV with immersive sound when you set up Alexa Home Cinema with compatible devices. Learn more about Alexa Home Cinema.

Designed to protect your privacy

Alexa and Echo devices are built with multiple layers of privacy protection. For example, Echo Studio has a Microphone Off button that electronically disconnects the microphones. You also have control over your voice recordings. Learn more about how you can view, hear or delete them at any time.

Simple to set up and use

Step 1

Place at least 15 cm from wall with clearance above and on all sides.

Step 2

Download the latest version of the Amazon Alexa app.

Step 3

Plug in your Echo Studio and wait for Alexa to greet you.

Step 4

Set up your device in the Alexa app.

Technical details

Echo Studio

Size

206 x 175 mm (height x diameter)

Weight

3.5 kg
Actual size and weight may vary by manufacturing process.

Audio

Three 51 mm midrange speakers, a 25 mm tweeter, a 133 mm woofer with bass aperture to maximise bass output.

Amplifier

Peak output 330 W; 24-bit DAC; 100 kHz bandwidth

Supported audio formats

FLAC, MP3, AAC, Opus, Vorbis, Dolby Digital, Dolby Digital Plus, Dolby Atmos and Sony 360 Reality Audio/MPEG-H; includes support for CD Quality (16-bit) and Hi-Res (up to 24-bit).

Supported music-streaming services

Amazon Music, Apple Music, Spotify, Deezer, TuneIn and more.

Automatic room adaptation

Analyses the acoustics of the room and continuously adjusts audio filters during music playback to optimise sound output regardless of placement (device must not be muted).

Spatial audio processing technology

Spatial audio processing technology is a digital audio processing technology that produces a more forward sound with greater width, clarity and presence that envelops the listener.

Audio input

Combination 3.5 mm mini-optical TOSLINK.

Fire TV compatibility

Connects wirelessly as the audio output for Fire TV - Learn more about compatibility Set up audio system using the Alexa app.

Wi-Fi connectivity

Dual-band Wi-Fi supports 802.11 a/b/g/n/ac (2.4 and 5 GHz) networks. Does not support connecting to ad-hoc (or peer-to-peer) Wi-Fi networks.

Smart home hub

Bluetooth Low Energy Mesh + Zigbee + Matter

Bluetooth connectivity

Advanced Audio Distribution Profile (A2DP) support for audio streaming from your mobile device to Echo or from Echo to your Bluetooth speaker. Audio/Video Remote Control Profile (AVRCP) to control connected mobile devices with voice. Hands-free voice control is not supported for Mac OS X devices. Bluetooth speakers requiring PIN codes are not supported.

Setup technology

Amazon Wi-Fi simple setup enables customers to connect smart devices to their Wi-Fi network in a few easy steps. Wi-Fi simple setup is another way Alexa is always getting smarter. Learn more about setup technology.

Warranty and service

Amazon Echo Studio is sold with a limited warranty of one year provided by the manufacturer. If you are a consumer, the limited warranty is in addition to your consumer rights, and does not jeopardise these rights in any way. This means you may still have additional rights at law even after the limited warranty has expired (click here for further information on your consumer rights). Use of Amazon Echo Studio is subject to the terms found here.

Accessibility features

The Alexa app and Alexa-enabled products include several features for customers with accessibility needs related to vision, hearing, mobility and speech. Learn more about Alexa accessibility.

Included in the box

Echo Studio, power cable and Quick Start Guide.

Privacy features

Wake word technology, streaming indicators, Microphone Off button, the ability to view and delete your voice recordings and more. Visit the Alexa Privacy Hub to explore how Alexa and Echo devices are designed to protect your privacy.

Language

Alexa speaks English, German, French, Italian and Spanish.

How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings, help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

Alex G
5.0 out of 5 stars Great Alexa Speaker with some Dolby Atmos tricks as well
Reviewed in the United Kingdom on 22 April 2020
Colour Name: CharcoalStyle Name: Device onlyVerified Purchase
OK same as with the sub, this is connected to a Fire 4K stick and an Amazon Echo Subwoofer.

Individual impressions first : it's a good looking device with classic Amazon mesh and the led top ring.

As an Alexa device it knows a few tricks.

Sound coming out of it is bright and bold and filles a room nicely.

The good:
1.Its Alexa powered so if you're into the personal assistant tred it's great;
2.Looks and feels good quality;
3.The sounds is good to great on it's own with bold soundstage and plenty of bass; good highs and mid reproduction as well and can be tweaked for more personalised sound;
4.On it's own does a good job but with add on echo sub it kills the home cinema experience with room filling sound that really is great; Dolby Atmos works great for this price category ;
5.Its fairly lound and sound field expansion works great to fill a small room or large studio apartment;
6.Nice set of controls with mute button at top
7. Can be combined with fire tv and sub to create a believable home cinema experience for movies;
8.Music sounds great but you can tell a slight difference when using Amazon's premium HD music service (both advantage and disadvantage)...
9.Decent connectivity with Bluetooth and Aux in/mini to slink optical input;
10. All round mics to pick up your voice works great but....

The bad:
1. It's a bit fiddly to set up and get going;
2. On it's own is completely Alexa dependant but with a fire stick the remote is a great addition and makes a difference ;
3. All rounds mics are good but they don't work well enough if there's too much noise around (even loud music can reduce their effectiveness) ;
4.Seams to struggle to keep connected sometimes; this thing really needs some great Wi-Fi to work properly (not always easy in the UK sadly; my sky wifi is not doing it any favours sometimes)
5. No sound sent to subwoofer from Aux or Bluetooth; big minus in my opinion
6. Sound though the optical in is not as loud and sometimes down right quiet; Also needs to be set to bitstream as Dolby output overwhelmed it (stops playing and keeps buffering like its trying to process the sound)
7. Surprisingly has some trouble connecting to my Huawei P30 pro over Bluetooth;
8. Good with music and movies but really needs HD music and 5.1 sound to shine (you can tell the difference on some tracks between Spotify and Amazon HD music using it which is good and bad at the same time);
9. The 3d sound is a bit fiddly experience with a hit and miss affair for me lis3to music;
10. Price. It's expensive and not too far off what the competitors are offering on its own. It does make more sense if you have other Amazon echo family devices but this also means its kinda limited to this ecosystem to work great.

Summary and conclusions:
Overall this is a good smart speaker with some great sound and a few nifty Alexa tricks. Unfortunately Alexa is also one of its minuses as its dependent on the Alexa Integration to work at its best. Same issue with the Echo family ecosystem they work great toghether but limit you to Amazon's offerings for the whole Dolby Atmos experience.

On its own it's a tad expensive and has a few quirks that hold it back a little...

But when you connect this thing with a fire stick 4k and echo sub this becomes a very interesting and tempting combination indeed.

PS. This can be connected to another Studio plus the Sub to make even better sound.

Roger
5.0 out of 5 stars For my requirements; All Round Perfection
Reviewed in the United Kingdom on 3 January 2024
Colour Name: Glacier WhiteStyle Name: Device onlyVerified Purchase
Having a number of Amazon Alexa devices around the home the Echo Studio has been on my radar for a long time and I have read the Spec and reviews too many times to count and on each occasion a review of one type or another plus the price has stopped me from purchasing.
Until now when I decided it was time to trial them for myself rather than be swayed by others and how pleased I am with my decision.
With my own experience of buying other Amazon Alexa devices and paired them for listening to music I was never going to buy just one Echo Studio so bit the bullet and decided to buy a pair. Amazon delivered the next day so there was no anxious waiting around for them to arrive.
They came extremely well packaged, not the shipping packing - this was actually quite poor considering the value and type of the product, the actual speakers came double boxed and in Amazon cloth bags to help lift them out as they are weighty. They have a real quality feel and look. I do agree with other reviews that the power cable needs updating but that’s my only criticism about the overall look. Before buying I compared the other speakers available and these appeal to me more than anything else out there regardless of price.
Unboxed and plugged in, they paired seamlessly with our network and Amazon account and connection took less than 5 minutes including an update they self performed. The sound quality is superb and we haven’t even pushed them over 50% as they are loud. A quick look at the Alexa app and a tweak on the EQ to suit my personal treble & bass choice and to pair them, not just together but with our Amazon fire stick and we sat back just to enjoy ‘all round perfection’ whilst watching tv via the fire stick.
We moved onto streaming some music tracks via Amazon Prime and Apple Music and were pleasantly surprised by the rich tones and extremely clear sound quality.
I reached out to Amazon for a suggestion re a good make of Optical cables and a Optical powered splitter in prep to link our tv to the Echo Optical input/s (you need two optical cables as a single cable will not provide sound to both speakers hence the required splitter too). Amazon suggested to purchase ‘any good quality cables and a powered splitter is recommended if the total cable length between the TV and both Echo Studios is more than 10 feet’. I only wanted to purchase a powered splitter anyway and found a nice triple output version with an additional 0.5mtr cable and a 5v USB power cable included with two 1.5 mtr Optical cables ordered too I would be all set to go when they arrived. I was apprehensive with this set up as I had read so many reviews whereupon others had experienced problems setting up this type of Optical connection.
My purchases arrived today and within 5 minutes everything was set up. I had already changed the tv output to optical because I had set up the optical tv out to a LG Sound bar (which to be honest wasn’t good and the sound lag was awful) so having now set up the Echo Studios with the tv I could wait to see what we faced?
I couldnt be more happy I was blown away with the sound quality. All the problems I had read about that other people say they experienced was not what I was now experiencing. I kept the tv running and just asked Alexa to play music and it switched perfectly and when that song finished I simply said ‘Alexa stop music’ and it switched back to the tv with no problem. It’s worth pointing out that the tv remote stops working the sound up/down/mute but you simply just voice control it and there is no voice lag between the tv picture and the Echo speakers unlike when using the sound bar. With the 3rd output on the splitter I can even plug in a set of headphones whereas I couldn’t do that prior as I had no headphone output via the tv. Cost of the 2 x cables £19.98 and the splitter £15.99 and worth every penny for the sound quality we are now getting via the Echo set up. And to top it all off the Echo Studios still work perfectly when asking Alexa to do anything (obviously the tv sound stops whilst this takes place but thereafter it simply switches back to tv sound.
I have no cons what so ever my only two regrets are not buying during Black Friday to save a few bob and for not buying before now.
The pros are quality sound now from the tv and streaming music and the two Echos are connecting to my iPad & Samsung phone to play music perfectly via Bluetooth.
So if you are in doubt about trying & buying just do it and see for yourself if they fit the bill for your needs. There’s a lot of help out there if you get stuck with set up or what accessories work and worse case scenario if you don’t get on with them you have time to simply return them.
I’m glad I took the gamble to try them for myself and I now have all round sound perfection from these great Echo Studio Speakers.
